  item-40 at level 1: text: The OTSL vocabulary is comprised of the following tokens:
  item-41 at level 1: list: group list
    item-42 at level 2: list_item: "C" cell - a new table cell that either has or does not have cell content
    item-43 at level 2: list_item: "L" cell - left-looking cell, me ... he left neighbor cell to create a span
    item-44 at level 2: list_item: "U" cell - up-looking cell, merg ... e upper neighbor cell to create a span
    item-45 at level 2: list_item: "X" cell - cross cell, to merge with both left and upper neighbor cells
    item-46 at level 2: list_item: "NL" - new-line, switch to the next row.
  item-47 at level 1: paragraph: A notable attribute of OTSL is t ... achieving lossless conversion to HTML.
  item-48 at level 1: section_header: Language Syntax
  item-49 at level 1: paragraph: The OTSL representation follows these syntax rules:
  item-50 at level 1: list: group list
    item-51 at level 2: list_item: Left-looking cell rule: 
The lef ... either another "L" cell or a "C" cell.
    item-52 at level 2: list_item: Up-looking cell rule:
The upper  ... either another "U" cell or a "C" cell.
    item-53 at level 2: list_item: Cross cell rule:
    item-54 at level 2: list_item: The left neighbour of an "X" cel ... ither another "X" cell or an "L" cell.
    item-55 at level 2: list_item: First row rule:
Only "L" cells and "C" cells are allowed in the first row.
    item-56 at level 2: list_item: First column rule:
Only "U" cell ... cells are allowed in the first column.
    item-57 at level 2: list_item: Rectangular rule:
The table repr ... of tokens, terminated with "NL" token.
  item-58 at level 1: paragraph: The application of these rules g ... icted sequence is syntactically valid.
